This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on July 24, 2020, marking the 70th anniversary of the start of the Korean War. The proclamation acknowledges the sacrifices made by American veterans who fought in the war and emphasizes the importance of the alliance between the United States and South Korea. It also designates July 27, 2020, as National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day and calls upon all Americans to honor and give thanks to Korean War veterans.